### **2️⃣ Early Electronic Computing (1900s-1940s)**

- **Turing Machine (1936)** – **Alan Turing’s** abstract model of computation.
- **ENIAC (1945)** – First general-purpose electronic computer, used in WWII.
- **COBOL & FORTRAN (1950s)** – Early high-level programming languages.

🔗 **Related Notes:**

